#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Sumanavagga"
msgstr "4. With Sumanā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Puttasutta"
msgstr "39. A Child"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.39:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, ṭhānāni sampassantā mātāpitaro puttaṃ icchanti kule "
"jāyamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, parents see five reasons to wish for the birth of a child in "
"the family."

msgctxt "an5.39:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.39:1.3"
msgid "Bhato vā no bharissati;"
msgstr "Since we looked after them, they’ll look after us."

msgctxt "an5.39:1.4"
msgid "kiccaṃ vā no karissati;"
msgstr "They’ll do their duty for us."

# At AN 7.52, etc. kulavamsa clearly means family tradition rather than family lineage.
msgctxt "an5.39:1.5"
msgid "kulavaṃso ciraṃ ṭhassati;"
msgstr "The family traditions will last."

msgctxt "an5.39:1.6"
msgid "dāyajjaṃ paṭipajjissati;"
msgstr "They’ll take care of the inheritance."

msgctxt "an5.39:1.7"
msgid "atha vā pana petānaṃ kālaṅkatānaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ anuppadassatīti."
msgstr ""
"Or else when we have passed away they’ll give an offering on our behalf."

msgctxt "an5.39:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca ṭhānāni sampassantā mātāpitaro puttaṃ icchanti "
"kule jāyamānanti."
msgstr ""
"Parents see these five reasons to wish for the birth of a child in the "
"family."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.1"
msgid "Pañca ṭhānāni sampassaṃ,"
msgstr "Seeing five reasons,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.2"
msgid "puttaṃ icchanti paṇḍitā;"
msgstr "astute people wish for a child."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.3"
msgid "Bhato vā no bharissati,"
msgstr "Since we looked after them, they’ll look after us."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.4"
msgid "kiccaṃ vā no karissati."
msgstr "They’ll do their duty for us."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.1"
msgid "Kulavaṃso ciraṃ tiṭṭhe,"
msgstr "The family traditions will last."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.2"
msgid "dāyajjaṃ paṭipajjati;"
msgstr "They’ll take care of the inheritance."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.3"
msgid "Atha vā pana petānaṃ,"
msgstr "Or else when we have passed away"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.4"
msgid "dakkhiṇaṃ anuppadassati."
msgstr "they’ll give an offering on our behalf."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.1"
msgid "Ṭhānānetāni sampassaṃ,"
msgstr "Seeing these five reasons"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.2"
msgid "puttaṃ icchanti paṇḍitā;"
msgstr "astute people wish for a child."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.3"
msgid "Tasmā santo sappurisā,"
msgstr "And so good people,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.4"
msgid "kataññū katavedino."
msgstr "grateful and thankful,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.44"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.1"
msgid "Bharanti mātāpitaro,"
msgstr "look after their parents,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.2"
msgid "pubbe katamanussaraṃ;"
msgstr "remembering what was done for them in the past."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.3"
msgid "Karonti nesaṃ kiccāni,"
msgstr "They do for their parents,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.4"
msgid "yathā taṃ pubbakārinaṃ."
msgstr "as their parents did for them in the past."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.1"
msgid "Ovādakārī bhataposī,"
msgstr "Following their advice, looking after those who raised them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.2"
msgid "kulavaṃsaṃ ahāpayaṃ;"
msgstr "the family traditions are not lost."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.3"
msgid "Saddho sīlena sampanno,"
msgstr "Faithful, accomplished in ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.4"
msgid "putto hoti pasaṃsiyo”ti."
msgstr "such a child is praiseworthy.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.39:6.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
